caption: (Translated by Google) I love the bills for this place! They are like being at home 🇦🇷 !!! I recommend all Argentines should go to this place. I have yet to go there for dinner and try their dishes, which will undoubtedly be very good.  (Original) Me encantan las facturas de este lugar! Son como estar en casa 🇦🇷!!! Recomiendo a todos los argentinos deben ir a este lugar. Aún debo ir a cenar allí y probar sus platos , que sin duda serán muy buenos.

Their "milanesas to-go-box" caught my attention. So I decided to give them a try. When I got there I was lucky to meet both owners, Chef Ettore and Manager Fernando. What a nice pair of people! We talked about a bunch of Argentina topics and I ended buying "a bit of everything". Let me tell you, the food quality and the flavors were TOP NOTCH. You should try them, too! Empanadas, facturas, milanesas... So yummy!!!
Fantastic and tasty food, I loved the mood the spot has, and the staff members were super friendly. Will definitely visit here next time.
Love this place, the food is amazing!!!!
The customer service is constantly prompt, great ambience, very welcoming staff members. I will return here again when I get in the area.
Very friendly staff and the food is delicious!

At the moment  you enter this place  the personel give you an excellent feeling. Very courteous hosts, it is a friendly place to hang out with friends or with your date. delightful  cuisine, qualified  chef, competitive  pay and nice  service. Warmly recommended.
This restaurant has superb service as well as yummy meals. One of the best restaurant in the city. The food and drinks served quickly and the rates were fair. Recommended.

Great cocktails, attentive service, and delicious food! I would highly recommend their risottos cooked perfectly with lobster, shrimp, or veggies and well seasoned. You always know authentic Italian when the meal is finished with free limoncello. Can't wait to return
This is a fantastic place to eat. The staff is very friendly and knowledgeable. A pleasure to dine here at all times. 🤗

I have always loved this little restruraunt. It is so quintessentially ITALIAN. The food is wonderful, and the waiters and people who work there are really lovely. I'm so glad Bethesda MD still has nice places like this. I'm REALLY glad that, even though the Pandemic is ongoing, La Panetteria is open and a great little getaway for the romantics out there. 5/5.
They were very friendly and the food was really good.

I can't love this place enough. Truly a gem. The owner head chef is very personable and creates uniquely delicious dishes.  This is definitely one of my top 5 restaurants I have visited in the last few years..
Delicious food, friendly hosts/service, big variety and selection in menu and reasonably priced wines, great experience overall.
Ordered take-out and was very pleased with a nice meal
Everything was great just one of the pasta meals tasted completely burnt.

Wonderful place, family owned and managed, they made our nigh special. Food was great, music simply perfect. We love this place, and the entire team, including Kendra, are lovely.  Highly recommended, we will be back soon!!! Thanks Hector

This is one of my favorite restaurants in the area. Since restaurants are closed for dining in, I’ve been ordering from the carry out menu and love their food. Dulce de leche crepes are out of this world 😋.
went with my husband to celebrate Valentyne`s Day.Even though the restorant was full, the food was served quickly. It was fresh and delicius

Came here around 2 weeks ago for my mother's birthday, and I forgot to write a review. The food is so fresh, and original recipes. This is a very classy place, you will not be disappointed. The customer service is the best I've seen in Montgomery County for an Italian restaurant. The waiter, the manager, all made sure we got top notch servicing. This was the day before Valentine's Day. They went above and beyond for us, and we will never forget it. I look forward to coming back here again soon, on a date night.
Great ambiance and delicious food.
Awesome experience as always!
It’s a nice cozy place, homely  feeling. Food was good too!
The food was great.

I went with my husband to celebrate Valentyne`s Day.Even though the restorant was full, the food was served quickly. It was fresh and delicius . We ordered spagetti Alfredo and chiken al Marsalla .The staff was very friendly, however I felt a little rush because we received the bill in advance .
Honestly some of the best food I've tasted. You can tell it is made from scratch. A little crowded, but that was probably cus of valentines day. The Orangecello is amazing
I recommend the Argentinian dishes. Big sizes and good prices. Very kind attention.

We met with friends at this place for lunch. we heard about this place from many people.  Well, it was very successful. The staff members were extremely nice and we had a great feeling. The meal was fresh and delicious. We enjoyed every moment and we shall absolutely come back again. we highly recommend this place.

This was my second time here, and the food was excellent once again. The pasta is homemade, the salads and antipasti were all delicious (the Caprese and the fried zucchini were our favorites). I would like to give them a 4.9, unfortunately the choice is a 4 or a 5, and I could not give them a 5 because the bar is lacking. I strongly suggest either wine or something on the rocks, because the liquor selection, and the mixed drinks were lacking. Otherwise, great food, great service, really nice people and a good experience all around.
Stood inside door 3 minutes before staff noticed me; once sat, waited TEN minutes for anyone to visit the table. Steak was overcooked. Very disappointing for a first visit.

I lived in Italy. And I’m impressed bythe creativity, food,ambience and service. My brother is a chef in Philadelphia so I am used to the work of talented chefs. I am delighted to say I found a hidden treasure. I will return frequently.  We had the pasta carbonara, eggplant ratatouille, the house salad with the pera al vino rosso for dessert. The meal was authentic, dessert was creative and the ambience was perfect.

My first time at the La Panetteria, the environment was very cozy, yet elegantly decorated. I order the Milanese carne, which came with French fries home made and a mixed salad.  my waiter was very helpful and always making sure everything was alright with my table. coming back soon . Also has an extensive menus going from pasta dishes to vegan dishes, as well has Argentine entrees. Highly recommend!!
Amazing food with great service, what more can you want?
The spot is wonderful and spacious, the meals was delicious and the prices were very fair. quickly, productive service and very affable staff members. I highly recommend this place.

We went for a holiday work lunch and it was everything you can imagine! The decor of the restaurant was absolutely stunning and even though it was cloudy outside, you entered, and felt transported to Italy! The wood, green plants, paintings and decor was spot on! And then the food - DELICIOUS! the waiters bought out the bread right away and bought seconds when we scarfed down our first loaf! The bread was soft and the olive oil bottle was so cute! I ordered the rigatoni alla caprese, and it was absolutely amazing! I ended my lunch with a cup of coffee and tiramisu🙌 I would highly recommend coming to this restaurant with your family, loved ones and your work family for any occasion! I will definitely be visiting back - need to try the mushroom ravioli!!!!

First of all The ambiance of this place is amazing.. everyone is friendly and warm and oh my god the food...being a fan of Italian food and having tried many Italian restaurants this place is by far the best I have been too... the marinara sauce was a whole new discovery... they serve the creamiest pasta and finally the dulche de leche crepe was the cherry on top..

The food was AMAZING. The decor was kinda worn and the restaurant was pretty empty, so I was concerned. The food is so good it doesnt matter. Cocktails and dessert were stellar also. The entire food experience was incredible, will definitely be back.

La Panetteria hosted our managers luncheon for 22 people.  We were offered a semi-private room which was perfect for our event!  The staff was very friendly and a pleasure to work with from start to finish - from the date/time availability inquiry, to the service, to the delicious food (a 3 course executive meal), to the final bill.  We'll be back for more corporate meals.
Had a good experience in this spot with my kids. The food comes out quick and the customer service is just fantastic. Prices are affordable.

We had excellent Chilean Sea Bass and grilled vegetable Lasagna, including sharing an insalata tricolore. The desert was also very good with a flan dulce de lechne and outstanding bread pudding. The servers were very helpful.This is not your typical italian restaurant.  We will be back with friends..November 2, 2019
Nice restaurant with a diverse menu. Slow but steady service.
We went in for a celebration and we had an AMAZING time. We were over 20 people: the rooms are GORGEOUS, the attention is impecable, and the food is superb! Totally recommend it!

(Translated by Google) If you like Italian and Argentinian food this is your place! Homemade and varied food at a good price, in a very cozy place. We were a large group of friends and the treatment was unbeatable. We will be back!  (Original) Si te gusta la comida italiana y argentina este es tu sitio! Comida casera y variada a buen precio, en un lugar muy acogedor. Fuimos un grupo grande d amigos y el trato fue inmejorable. Volveremos!

Last Sunday a friend celebrated his birthday and the experience was really pleasant: the food and the service are high quality. We were around 20 adults and kids, and everything went very smoothly. I would really recommend it if you want to have Argentinian-Italian cuisine.
Horrible and Unprofessional Management. From 1 to 10 I'll give this a -1

We came to this restaurant for a meeting. my friend recommended this spot.  Well, we were not disappointed. the crew were so friendly and we had a fantastic feeling. The food was just great. We loved this place a lot and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Recommended.

Such amazing food!! Would highly recommend. There are quite a few "fusion" places that actually don't mesh very well but this place combined the best of Italian and Argentinean cuisine! They also have a great selection of wine and the service is incredibly friendly.

(Translated by Google) Very pretty place!!! Very good food, prices very well, attention is very good, completely recommended! To go as a couple, family or friends.  (Original) Muy lindo lugar!!! Muy buena comida, los precios muy bien, la atención es muy buena, completamente recomendable! Para ir en pareja, familia o amigos.
Great new place in Bethesda.  Been there once and looks quite promising.
Attentive, polite staff and great food! This is our go to spot for celebratory dinners
Lava chocolate cake with ice cream!

The service at one of our favorite downtown Bethesda restaurants was exemplary.  Unfortunately the time it took to receive our 2 entrees and salad was excessively long.  We came to learn that the location changed hands and is now an Argentinian-Italian eatery.  We're hoping the order time improves soon.

Great place! My family has been going here for years. The store has recently changed management but the food is just as good, Fernando was an excellent host and gave us drinks on the house at the end of our me
Great food, little slow service
Had a first date with a hotty here. Food was excellent!
Had a great experience here with my daughter. The food comes quickly and the customer service is just good. Prices are affordable.
I always arrive getting some food here. I liked the swift service and well prepared food. Great work.
When I was their it was quite. I liked the silence
(Translated by Google) The food is very good. Very good attention. Congratulations  (Original) Muy buena la comida. Muy buena la atencion. Felicitaciones

It's a great place for family and friends, we went to celebrate an occasion! The food was the best ever! The zucchini fritti, Chicken Alfredo, Argentinian steak-Milanesa De Carne was the best I've ever tasted.. to top it with Tiramisu and the molten Chocolate cake!! The food is cooked to perfection, spectacular presentation and great service! The owners are so involved and friendly! Must try this place!
Great service, decent prices (for Bethesda), delicious food

Came for a wine tasting dinner last night.  5 courses really well paired with the wines.  Excellent food and wine.  Service was really friendly and welcoming.  We live around the corner so she be coming again :)
I eat in this spot a lot since I work nearby. I got to say their service is always excellent and they keep the place well organized consistently. Prices are reasonable and they serve big portions.

A must-try in Bethesda. La Panetteria offers a great combination of fine cuisine at a reasonable price, great wine choices, authentic decor, great service and atmosphere. Its menu has been updated and it offers a good variety of choices. The dessert menu is amazing and you probably will want to come back to try all of the options it has. The owners and the staff will make sure you have a lovely experience.
This place never fails to impress. They have fantastic food for affordable pricing, there are no long waits even when the spot is loaded.
Food was amazing!!!!!!!! It’s very cozy and romantic restaurant for a family or for a date. If you’re looking for good food and great atmosphere this is your place

This place used to be an Italian restaurant treasure, but it has recently diversified to serve both Italian and Argentine cuisine.  The two styles don't mix well, and the Italian dishes that used to  be so good are now completely bland.
Service was excellent. Kind and friendly people. Good food.

I was a regular,and I have returned three times since the reopening I miss Harry and Corey,  but the wait staff has been  retained. The service is still great. There are still Italian favorites,  but now there are Argentine dishes as well.if you like steak and malted, you should try the menu.the beautiful decor has not changed.though it is not the same, it is still a wonderful place to eat.and the chef has come and talked to me each visit. He promises I can still get my ravioli
We go to La Panetteria on a regular basis.  Restaurant is pleasant, nice staff, well-prepared food, decent prices.
(Translated by Google) Cozy place, exquisite food! very good attention.  (Original) Lugar  acogedor,exquisita comida!  muy buena atencion.
Beautiful place and delicious food options

Mr. Fernando, this was actually after the change. *** I am editing my review. The staff are reasonably friendly, but the service was extremely slow. We had to repeat our requests for bread and our check. Additionally (this was the larger concern), my husband's lasagna had a piece of plastic in it, which is both dangerous and unappetizing to say the least. We will probably not return. *** Food was great, but unfortunately we were seated next to an extremely rude and racist couple who bashed immigrants (despite the staff who are immigrants). Hope to never see him again. I wish the manager and owner had stood up for the staff.
Wonderful atmosphere, courteous staff and delicious food!!! My expectations were definitely surpassed.

My wife and I went here for Valentines day last month. Let me tell you, it was fantastic.  Quiet and quaint ambiance, and excellent food. My wife is Korean and she really enjoyed their take on the Grilled Calamari.  A little bit pricey, but that's what you should expect in Bethesda. Would highly recommend.
No real complaints.  Not bad.  I have had better.
Great food, convenient location. The pesto fettuccini was fantastic. Their prices have gone up since the last time they posted the menu but only a $1-2 per entree. I would come back if I lived here
Very good, cozy atmosphere

I absolutely adore this place. I eat here several times a month. Mondays - bottles of wine are half price. the staff treats me like family. the food is excellent. they remember little things like I like ice with my sparkling water. they have even changed menu items at suggestion. they listen, and they care. if you go and eat once, you will go back. decor is beautiful- so it is a great date night place, but i can also go by myself and know I won't feel alone or out of place. I usually start with soup or an appetizer , then do a half order of ravoli, then an entree (often a special) and I always finish with dessert. The pastas you can have marinara, cream or amore' sauce. There are a lot of seafood options, and though I do eat meat they have several vegetarian options as well. I recently tried their white pizza which was excellent - there is truly something for everyone
Classic Italian food with good service and great specials : Desert a la carte and very good chianti and coffee!!!!
Delicious lasagna! Loved the white pizza! Excellent service!
We love this place!
Mediocre service and food. Beautiful location and interior touches. Very courtesy staff and fast food preparation and service. Visited during a mid afternoon lunch.
Best service and good food !!!
Just okay. Food was a bit too salty and lacked a bit flavor.... Sorry. The restaurant needs updating as well.
Always enjoyed this consistent and reliable restaurant.
Excellent fresh bread, great lasagna with plenty of marinara sauce  and great service .
Very reasonable prices with delicious food.

Very nice Italian gem in Bethesda. The food is authentic and their desserts are excellent. I love their employees (Especially Corey)who really know how to make customers feel at home. I definitely will return soon.
Yum. We've lived in Bethesda for nearly 25 years and have never been to this gem of a restaurant. Everything was delicious. Our server was delightful.
Food was good and they were very kind and went out of their way for us.
Food was delicious , service was very attentive,  prices were very reasonable
Super cute date night restuarant. The staff was very friendly and attentive. The food was delicious and the wine was half price!
Great service and specials
Bearing in mind rather bad Italian cuisine in Bethesda it was a pleasant surprise. Worth a try with decent portions and good aftertaste.
Good Italian
We returned after a very long time (years).  Quaint and cozy dining room.  Parking would be better in the evening.
Eh, both food and service are so-so. Over-priced!

Sat down to have mother's day dinner here after making a reservation and we got served water and bread for 30 mins. No drink orders or food orders were placed or taken. We sat up front and they never came by to take our orders, so we left (group of 7).
Great food and amazing service. It's great for parties.
(Translated by Google) Excellent!  (Original) Excelente!
Good  food
Delicious classic Italian food with friendly service who knows your name. Romantic and good for the family.

I love the ambiance of the restaurant. We went in the day time and the place was adequately lit and it made the scenery magnificent. The food was exquisite and was served on time and affordable. Great staff with great attitudes. Will definitely be visiting here again!
Just meh... the decor is reminiscent of an old school Italian eatery in Milan, but the food leaves a lot to be desired.

My husband and I went for the first time with my brother and his wife - the food was delicious (they made a few modifications to suit some of us) and the service was great. The restaurant itself is quite pleasant and has a nice ambience.

The food was exceptionally good but we had some confusion and mix ups with service. Also, hard to find parking nearby (closest garage was full) and no valet made the experience that much more frustrating
Their food was so really good authentic Italian,  it has good ingredients and cooked to perfection.delectable. The waiters are very friendly and kind. We had a really amazing time here.
Always a delicious meal. Staff is great and the specials are always a hit!

I always enjoy going to the this restaurant. The food is always good. I had the Special, Roletini Pescotore. Tortellini stuffed with Crab and lobster served with Amore sauce and melted mozzarella. Yum! Our Server was very pretty, friendly and nice. I would highly recommend this restaurant.
Awesome place, ambience, food andcrowd

Racist owner. Who cares how good the food is when you're going to be discriminated against and made to feel uncomfortable in your own skin. Terrible service, I felt sick to my stomach after leaving. This is 2018 people.

My heart broke on Valentine's Day to learn my daughter invited by her wonderful boyfriend to "romantic" dinner at this establishment was treated so horribly. They were told by the manager that the other customers behind them were "paying" customers and were seated for dinner. My daughter and her boyfriend were not seated for dinner with the assumption they cannot afford their meal. Both from Texas in DC highly educated and starting their careers, both employed, and why should I have to bring up their resumé to make this point. They just wanted to be seated for dinner. Why was this too difficult a task for this establishment. La Panetteria, you didn't just ruin Valentine's Day 2018 for my daughter and her boyfriend, you reminded us we have so much work to do to fix maladaptive attitudes that are harmful to our society and to your business. Because I for one will make sure everyone knows about your establishment for this racist experience. You will be surprised at the power of peaceful protest.
Found this place while looking for some Italian restaurants while visiting my family.  Great atmosphere and delicious food. Will visit again.
Great service. A bit too much mozzarella in the dishes.
Warm, friendly service with delicious food.

I've eaten here at La Panetteria three times, and each time has been outstanding. The food is amazing, and four of us trade off bites just from bliss. "You gotta try this." "Oh that is so good." "Here, try this." Etc. Service is always wonderful too. Even the water and plate removal guy smiles warmly and seems happy to be helping us. Place is nicely decorated with pleasant Italian atmosphere, but not overly starched. Just a great experience.
Food is good. Attentive service
Terrific
Good staff, quiet, good food. Althogub I had the fetty Alfredo and it was a bit buttery. Overall very good recommend

Every time I go here to eat whether its to buy a salad at lunch or sit down to dinner, the food is EXCEPTIONAL...the customer service is great! The owner is super nice and the food is made with love! I would highly recommend this place to anyone. The prices are SUPER reasonable for Bethesda and the portions are always VERY generous. I can never finish it but I always enjoy it later. GO! You won't regret it!
Very beautiful environment and delicious food
Excellent food!
Basic Italian, done well.

The food and wine here are delicious. My only complaint was that it was a little hot inside. They had no fans or AC running like no one else cared that it was hot. We asked them to turn it on and that was that.
Wonderful food, great service, lovely ambience.
Old school staff, fairly attentive good overall dishes
Food is good, drinks good. Service very good. Recommended
Fabulous food, wonderful family atmosphere, but appropriate for date night, too!
Wonderful food & service!

I have been eating at La Panetteria for many years and always have had a wonderful experience.  This is an authentic Italian restaurant with excellent food, great pasta, good bread and good portions. The staff is awesome and the prices are very reasonable. I highly recommend you try it. Once you do, you will want to come back again and again.
Great lamb, which is unusual in the area. People liked the pasta as well. Will come back to try new dishes.
Very cozy loved the food.

Delicious pasta!!! By far one of the best places to get genuine Italian food. Very delicious. I had the Ravioli Di Portabella. Sooooooo good, cream sauce was the most delicious sauce I have ever tasted!  A must visit if you're in bethesda!

You should eat here! The food was great and so was the wine. The service was excellent from the second we walked in the door until we left, everyone was so friendly. The atmosphere was great, very quaint. I will definitely be going back!
Very good delicious rib eye steak . I recommend this restaurant for its reasonably priced and good food.

Underwhelming experience. Went in with high expectations, but ended up having a dinner that could have been from Anytown, America. Tasted like frozen vegetables warmed up, lamb was overcooked and tough, grilled calamari was flavorless, and the pasta was about what you get when making it at home. The Antipasto was good!

I love this beautiful place so much. I live 45 minutes to an hour away and have been there twice. The dessert is phenomenal, and the staff is amazing. A true gentleman served us, in a tux and tie. :) delicious salads, pastas, amazing.
Looks a bit Olive Garden but has very good, authentic food.

When we entered the restaurant on a Friday night there were only two other diners; that should have been a clue. I ordered Spaghetti Carabonara. It was inedible. My companion ordered a salad whose slice of pickled beet was far superior to the tasteless tomatoes, tired cucumbers, and wilted lettuce. It was my first and last visit to this restaurant. I'd advise you to eat elsewhere; the neighborhood is full of GOOD eateries.

I love their food.  It's cozy, but it's downtown Bethesda; what isn't cozy there?!  It has a nice atmosphere.  It's nice and quiet, and a great place to meet with clients, or just go out with your coworkers.

My husband and I have been eating at La Panetteria for the last eight years and have had consistently wonderful experiences.  The very first time we ate there we were standing on the street, reading the menu, and a stranger passing by said, "Don't question it, just go in and eat.  You'll thank me!"  They were totally correct.  Authentic Italian, awesome staff, and the food, all the way from the bread to the dessert tray, will keep you coming back for more.  Don't question, go and try it!  You'll thank me. =)
Good I ate all my food!
Great homemade pasta at a reasonable price-that's all you need to know!
The best italian resturant you will find. Go here. We have come here 3 times and each has been fantastic. A wonderfull italian restaurant, cannot speak highly enough of it.

Hands down the best meal my wife and I have had since we've moved to the greater DC area.  Actually, aside from a dinner we enjoyed in Hawaii that cost three times the price, this was probably the best meal we have had.  The grilled lamb (surprisingly large portion) and squid were both exceedingly excellent.  Even the side dish of pasta was very good (usually its mediocre at best).  We enjoyed their house salad dressing and the desserts (tiramisu and flan) were amazing.  The service was also fantastic.
This cute little family Italian restaurant is the bigest secret in Bethesda.

Very beautiful setting. Food was good but not necessarily incredible. I had the veal tortellini. The tortellinis were good but the tomato sauce was a bit plain. The homemade salad dressing was amazing!! The service was very quick. If the water got low, it would immediately be filled, etc.
